    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Avon was renamed from Hartford in 1808 to avoid confusion with another New York town of the same name.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.villageofavonny.gov/about"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The native village Ga-no-wa-gas, meaning “stinking waters,” highlighted the sulfur springs that once made Avon a healing resort.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
